                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12948587" author="gertvanthienen" created="Fri, 29 Aug 2008 07:13:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The current fix handles an InputStream being sent as the message body correctly, but I think we should also handle other kinds of streaming data (StaxSource, Reader, ...).  How about using the same as the interceptor logic from the StreamCachingInterceptor?  We still have to find a way to reset the stream between redelivery attempts (adding a reset() method to the StreamCache interface perhaps?)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12948622" author="njiang" created="Sat, 30 Aug 2008 01:28:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added the unit test to show how the Source, Read, InputStream can be cached with StreamCache.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
